Package: censusapi
Title: Retrieve data from the Census APIs
Version: 0.1.0.9002
Authors@R: person("Hannah", "Recht", email = "hrecht2@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a wrapper to retrieve data from any Census API and
	return a data frame. getCensus's internal functions handle getting more
	than fifty variables at a time, overcoming a limitation of the APIs.
	Metadata functions return information on all available Census APIs,
	as well as geographies and variables available for a given API.
URL: https://github.com/hrecht/censusapi
BugReports: https://github.com/hrecht/censusapi/issues
Depends: R (>= 3.0.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Imports:
    httr,
    jsonlite,
    XML
Suggests: testthat
